# Friend System Implementation Analysis

This document provides the complete understanding needed to implement the ignore list feature by mirroring the existing friend system.

---

## 1. FriendStore: `/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/wow/friend-store.ts`

The store is the in-memory model for the friends list. It is completely self-contained with a Map keyed by `bigint` GUID and a single listener callback.

**Type definitions (lines 1-21):**

```typescript
export type FriendEntry = {
  guid: bigint;
  name: string;
  note: string;
  status: number;
  area: number;
  level: number;
  playerClass: number;
};

export type FriendEvent =
  | { type: "friend-list"; friends: FriendEntry[] }
  | { type: "friend-online"; friend: FriendEntry }
  | { type: "friend-offline"; guid: bigint; name: string }
  | { type: "friend-added"; friend: FriendEntry }
  | { type: "friend-removed"; guid: bigint; name: string }
  | { type: "friend-error"; result: number; name: string };
```

**Class structure (lines 23-92):**

- `private friends: Map<bigint, FriendEntry>` — storage
- `private listener?: (event: FriendEvent) => void` — single event subscriber
- `onEvent(cb)` — registers the listener
- `set(entries)` — replaces the entire list, fires `friend-list`
- `add(entry)` — inserts one entry (copy), fires `friend-added`
- `update(guid, fields)` — partial update; fires `friend-online` (status != 0) or `friend-offline` (status == 0); no-op if GUID not found
- `remove(guid)` — deletes entry, fires `friend-removed`; no-op if GUID not found
- `setName(guid, name)` — mutates name in-place, no event (used by deferred name resolution)
- `findByName(name)` — case-insensitive linear scan, returns `FriendEntry | undefined`
- `all()` — returns sorted-by-name snapshot

**For the ignore list:** The `IgnoreStore` will be much simpler. Ignored entries have no status/area/level/class fields in the contact list (the server sends only GUID, flags, and note for ignored contacts). The store only needs: `set(entries)`, `add(name)`, `remove(guid)`, `has(guidLow)`, `all()`, and a single `IgnoreEvent` union.

